    "notes": "A delightful white wine that showcases the best of Burgundy's Chardonnay grape. With a pale golden hue, this wine has a captivating aroma of fresh red apples, honey, and white flowers that immediately captures the senses. On the palate, it offers an exquisite taste with elegant and rich flavors of toasted nuts and citrus that provide a perfect balance of acidity and minerality. This wine is a true representation of the region's terroir, where the limestone soil and cool climate provide ideal growing conditions for Chardonnay grapes. This wine is an excellent choice to pair with a variety of foods. Its rich flavors and balanced acidity complement roasted salmon, shellfish, and creamy cheeses exceptionally well. It also pairs nicely with lighter dishes, such as grilled vegetables or chicken, making it a versatile option for any meal.",
    "year": 2023,
    "wine_type": "white",
    "grapes": [
      1
    ]
  }
},
{
