    "notes": "This is a serious Margaux, hugely Cabernet dominant on both nose and palate as you would expect with 94% of the blend. It has an extremely fine, elongated tannic structure, barely perceptible yet classy, with a focus on gentle elasticity. There are more blue than black fruits here, wonderfully spun out and softened with crushed tobacco. It has the expansive aromatic structure of Margaux, the floral and mineral aspects clear, as is the tension that lifts the palate up and out. It's reminiscent of 2005, though with less evident tannins. It's not as hefty as the 2010 or as staggering as the 2015, but it is still a joyful expression of the estate. 1% Petit Verdot completes the blend.",
    "year": 2016,
    "wine_type": "red",
